Text Formatting
===============
You can make text _bold_, make it look *italic*.  However, for function names
you might prefer the `typewriter` style. Note that within typewriter style
all other text attributes get ignored, e.g. in `_bold_` or ''_bold_'' you can
use underscores for variable names or an expression like `3*5=15` and so on.

You [[also]] con combine *_attributes_* in _*arbitrary*_ order. This also can be
used within a word, e.g. in _Donau*schiff*fahrt*gesellschaft*_ for emphasizing
substrings. Here a  __Link with some _bold_ and *italic* subtext__.


