Nested Lists
============
Here we have a simple list with items and sub-items:
    - Creating lists is very easy.  You simply start some line with a dash.
      Just look at the `DocTool` source code.
    - Every line starting with a dash creates a new item
        - Increasing the indent level creates sub items
        - You can have as many sub items as you want
    - Decreasing the indent level creates another item on the 
      top level.
      
      Of course an item can have more than one paragraph.  The indent
      level therefore is important to make clear that a paragraph belongs
      to the last list item

     Note that a newline or an indent is required before you can start
     a list.


