Lists with Tables
=================
Here a list where some items contain tables

    - Within a block you can start a new block by increasing the indent. Here
      we are inside a list item and start a table block:
       +-------+--------------------+----------+
       | Rank  | Name               | Time     |
       +=======+====================+==========+
       | 1     | Michael Lehn       |  1:12.32 |
       +-------+--------------------+----------+
       | 2     | Iris Häcker        |  1:14.54 |
       +-------+--------------------+----------+
       | 3     | Schalke            | 14:14.54 |
       +-------+--------------------+----------+
      Now we are back in the list item by decreasing the indent. This way you
      can write your document very compact.

    - You also can start a new block by separating the list item's paragraph
      from the list items table by an empty line.  This is done here

      +-------+--------------------+----------+
      | Rank  | Name               | Time     |
      +=======+====================+==========+
      | 1     | Michael Lehn       |  1:12.32 |
      +-------+--------------------+----------+
      | 2     | Iris Häcker        |  1:14.54 |
      +-------+--------------------+----------+
      | 3     | Schalke            | 14:14.54 |
      +-------+--------------------+----------+
      
      Again we are back in the list item as we used another empty line.

    - Of course you can combine both, i.e. increase the indent and an empty
      line

          +-------+--------------------+----------+
          | Rank  | Name               | Time     |
          +=======+====================+==========+
          | 1     | Michael Lehn       |  1:12.32 |
          +-------+--------------------+----------+
          | 2     | Iris Häcker        |  1:14.54 |
          +-------+--------------------+----------+
          | 3     | Schalke            | 14:14.54 |
          +-------+--------------------+----------+
      
      Just use whatever makes you document most readable.

    - The following table is outside the list.  That's because its indentation
      is too small.

    +-------+--------------------+----------+
    | Rank  | Name               | Time     |
    +=======+====================+==========+
    | 1     | Michael Lehn       |  1:12.32 |
    +-------+--------------------+----------+
    | 2     | Iris Häcker        |  1:14.54 |
    +-------+--------------------+----------+
    | 3     | Schalke            | 14:14.54 |
    +-------+--------------------+----------+


